    "## 2 Preprocessing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "### 2.1. filter, normalize, scale & PCA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "filtered out 21848 genes that are detected in less than 335.38 cells\n",
      "normalizing counts per cell\n",
      "Normalization step is finished in adata.X\n",
      "Log transformation step is finished in adata.X\n",
      "Scale step is finished in adata.X\n",
      "PCA is done! Generated in adata.obsm['X_pca'], adata.uns['pca'] and adata.varm['PCs']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "st.pp.filter_genes(data,min_cells=0.01*data.n_vars)\n",
    "st.pp.normalize_total(data)\n",
    "data.obsm['normalized'] = pd.DataFrame(data.X.toarray(), index=data.obs_names, columns=data.var_names)\n",
    "st.pp.log1p(data)\n",
    "st.pp.scale(data)\n",
    "st.em.run_pca(data,n_comps=50)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 2.2. add morphology information"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The morphology feature is added to adata.obsm['X_morphology']!\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The data adjusted by morphology is added to adata.obsm['X_pca_morphology']\n",
      "Created k-Nearest-Neighbor graph in adata.uns['neighbors'] \n",
      "Added tissue image to the object!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "st.pp.tiling(data,out_path=\"./temp_tiling\",crop_size=40)\n",
    "st.pp.extract_feature(data)\n",
    "st.spatial.morphology.adjust(data,use_data='X_pca',radius=50,method=\"mean\")\n",
    "st.pp.neighbors(data,n_neighbors=25,use_rep='X_pca_morphology')\n",
    "# upload image without background for plotting\n",
    "st.add.image(adata=data, imgpath=\"C:\\\\Users\\\\uqjxu8\\\\GIH\\\\Bioinformatics\\\\SPA\\\\Data\\\\visium\\\\Human_Breast_Cancer_Block_A_Section_1\\\\spatial\\\\tissue_hires_nobg.png\")"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "#### Compare the immune cells identified by the label transfer and the CCI clustering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "0.4043270890677005\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "immune_cci = data.obs['lr_neighbours_louvain'].copy()\n",
    "immune_cci = immune_cci.cat.set_categories(immune_cci.cat.categories.tolist()+['immune','non-immune'])\n",
    "immune_cci[immune_cci!=data.uns['lr_neighbours_louvain_max']] = 'non-immune'\n",
    "immune_cci[immune_cci==data.uns['lr_neighbours_louvain_max']] = 'immune'\n",
    "\n",
    "immune_label = data.obs['predictions'].copy()\n",
    "immune_label[immune_label.isin(['Bcell', 'Tcell', 'macrophage'])] = 'immune'\n",
    "immune_label[immune_label!='immune'] = 'non-immune'\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics.cluster import adjusted_rand_score\n",
    "print(adjusted_rand_score(immune_cci, immune_label))"
   ]
  },
